{
  "doc_id": "38623",
  "text": "The differentially expressed immune-related genes and TFs in HCC and normal tissues were detected using the Wilcoxon test method in R. |log2 foldchange| > 1 and FDR < 0.05 were considered as significant. Heatmaps were generated using pheatmap package and volcano plots were also conducted in R software. To assess the potential biologic functions of differentially expressed immune-related genes, Gene Ontology (GO) [CITATION_1] and Kyoto Encyclopedia of Genes and Genomes (KEGG) pathway enrichment analysis [CITATION_2] were performed by the cluster Profiler package [CITATION_3] in R. Functional categories with a adjusted P value < 0.05 were considered as significant pathways.",
